Measurements of the magnetic torque τ  = μ0VM × H have a high sensitivity for the detection of magnetic anisotropy, where μ0 is space permeability, V is the sample volume, and M is the magnetisation induced by external magnetic field H (Fig. 2a, see also Methods section). Torque is a thermodynamic observable that is equal to the derivative of the free energy with respect to angular displacement. Torque measurements performed for a range of directions of H within the tetragonal ab plane of Hg1201 test whether or not the pseudogap state breaks the fourfold crystal symmetry. In this configuration, τ is a periodic function of twice the azimuthal angle ϕ measured from the a axis:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
